{"title_page": "All India Senior School Certificate Examination", "text_new": "{{Infobox examination\n| name                = All India Senior School Certificate Examination\n| image_name          = [[File: CBSE_Logo.jpg]]\n| image_size          = 200px\n| image_alt           = Central Board of Secondary Education\n| caption             = Central Board of Secondary Education\n| acronym             = AISSCE\n| type                = Paper-based standardized test\n| test_admin          = [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]\n| skills_tested       = Languages, Humanities, Mathematics, Sciences, Skill Subjects, General Studies, Health and Physical Education, Work Experience\n| purpose             = Admission to undergraduate programs in universities or colleges\n| year_started        = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY}} -->\n| year_terminated     = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| duration            = 3 hours (per subject)\n| score_range         = 165-500\n| score_validity      = \n| offered             = Yearly\n| attempt_restriction =\n| regions             = '''India:'''<br>Delhi<br>Chennai<br>Guwahati<br>Ajmer<br>Panchkula<br>Allahabad<br>Patna<br>Bhubaneswar<br>Thiruvananthapuram<br>Dehradun<br><br>'''Middle East:'''<br>Bahrain<br>Iran<br>Oman<br>Qatar<br>Saudi Arabia<br>United Arab Emirates<br>Yemen<br><br>'''Foreign:'''<br>Afghanistan<br>Bangladesh<br>Burma<br>Ethiopia<br>Indonesia<br>Iran<br>Japan<br>Kuwait<br>Libya<br>Malaysia<br>Nepal<br>Nigeria<br>Republic of Benin<br>Russia<br>Singapore<br>Tanzania<br>Thailand<br>Uganda<br>West Africa\n| language            = English/Hindi\n| test_takers         = 1218393 (2019)\n| prerequisite        = Intended for Class 12 Students in CBSE-affiliated institutions\n| fee                 =  \n| score_users         = Colleges and universities; for undergraduate programs\n| qualification_rate  = 83.4% (2019)\n| free_label          = \n| free                = \n| website             = {{URL|cbse.nic.in}}\n| footnotes           =  \n}}\n\nThe '''All India Senior School Certificate Examination''' (AISSCE), colloquially known as the '''12<sup>th</sup> boards''', is a [[standardized test|standardized high-school completion examination]] conducted every year by the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]. The AISSCE assesses Class 12 students enrolled in CBSE-affiliated institutions. It is widely used for admissions to undergraduate programs in colleges and universities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://school.careers360.com/exams/cbse-class-12th?utm_source=google&utm_medium=kg|title=Central Board of Secondary Education Class 12th Examination|last=|first=|date=|website=Careers360|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nCBSE requires students to take five subjects which are externally assessed in Class 12, plus some internally assessed subjects (general studies, work experience and physical and health education). Students must pass each subject to gain their full qualification. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qips.ucas.com/qip/india-higher-secondary-school-certificate|title=India: Higher Secondary School Certificate|last=|first=|date=|website=UCAS Qualification Information Profiles|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n=== External Assessment ===\nThe Senior School Certificate Examination covers the entire syllabus of Class 12. Grades are awarded on the basis of a 9-point grading system in each scholastic subject as follows: <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=18-19}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\nGrading Scale for Scholastic Areas\n!Grade\n!Criteria\n|-\n|A1\n|Top {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|A2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|B1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|B2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|C1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|C2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|D1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|D2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|E\n|(Unspecified)\n|}\n\n=== Internal Assessment ===\nInternal Assessment in different subjects will be as per details given in the syllabus for each subject:\n\n==== Assessment of Co-Scholastic Areas ====\nStudents are assessed on three areas, i.e. General Studies, Health and Physical Education, and Work Experience.\n\n== Subjects ==\nStudents can choose a minimum of five subjects in Class 11, for which they are required to write the AISSCE in Class 12. \n\nSubjects are offered as follows:<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=13-18}}</ref>\n\n==== Languages (Group-L)====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 001: English Elective\n* 301: English Core\n* 002: Hindi Elective\n* 302: Hindi Core\n* 003: Urdu Elective\n* 303: Urdu Core\n* 022: Sanskrit Elective\n* 322: Sanskrit Core\n* 104: Punjabi\n* 105: Bengali\n* 106: Tamil\n* 107: Telugu\n* 108: Sindhi\n* 109: Marathi\n* 110: Gujarati\n* 111: Manipuri\n* 112: Malayalam\n* 113: Odia\n* 114: Assamese\n* 115: Kannada\n* 116: Arabic\n* 117: Tibetan\n* 118: French\n* 120: German\n* 121: Russian\n* 123: Persian\n* 124: Nepali\n* 125: Limboo\n* 126: Lepcha\n* 189: Telugu Telangana\n* 192: Bodo\n* 193: Tangkhul\n* 194: Japanese\n* 195: Bhutia\n* 196: Spanish\n* 197: Kashmiri\n* 198: Mizo\n{{div col end}}\n\n==== Academic Subjects (Group-A) ====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 027: History\n* 028: Political Science\n* 029: Geography\n* 030: Economics\n* 031: Carnatic Music Vocal\n* 032: Carnatic Music Mel. Ins.\n* 033: Carnatic Per. Ins. Mridangam\n* 034: Hindustani Music Vocal\n* 035: Hindustani Music Mel. Ins.\n* 036: Hindustani Per. Ins.\n* 037: Psychology\n* 039: Sociology\n* 041: Mathematics\n* 241: Applied Mathematics\n* 042: Physics\n* 043: Chemistry\n* 044: Biology\n* 045: Biotechnology\n* 046: Engineering Graphics\n* 048: Physical Education\n* 049: Painting\n* 050: Graphics\n* 051: Sculpture\n* 052: Applied/Commercial Art\n* 054: Business Studies\n* 055: Accountancy\n* 056: Kathak (Dance)\n* 057: Bharatnatyam (Dance)\n* 058: Kuchipudi (Dance)\n* 059: Odissi (Dance)\n* 060: Manipuri (Dance)\n* 061: Kathakali (Dance)\n* 064: Home Science\n* 065: Informatics Practices\n* 083: Computer Science\n* 066: Entrepreneurship\n* 073: Knowledge Tradition and Practices of India\n* 074: Legal Studies\n* 076: National Cadet Corps (NCC)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==== Skill Subjects (Group-S) ====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 802: Information Technology\n* 803: Web Application\n* 804: Automotive\n* 805: Financial Markets Management\n* 806: Tourism\n* 807: Beauty and Wellness\n* 808: Agriculture\n* 809: Food Production\n* 810: Front Office Operations\n* 811: Banking\n* 812: Marketing\n* 813: Health Care\n* 814: Insurance\n* 816: Horticulture\n* 817: Typography and Computer Application\n* 818: Geospatial Technology\n* 819: Electrical Technology\n* 820: Electronic Technology\n* 821: Media\n* 822: Taxation\n* 823: Cost Accounting\n* 824: Office Procedures and Practices\n* 825: Shorthand (English)\n* 826: Shorthand (Hindi)\n* 827: Air-conditioning and Refrigeration\n* 828: Medical Diagnostics\n* 829: Textile Design\n* 830: Design\n* 831: Salesmanship\n* 833: Business Administration\n* 834: Food Nutrition and Dietetics\n* 835: Mass Media Studies\n* 836: Library and Information Science\n* 837: Fashion Studies\n* 841: Yoga\n* 842: Early Childhood Education\n* 843: Artificial Intelligence\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Combination of Subjects===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Combination of Subjects <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=11-12}}</ref>\n!Serial No.\n!Name of Subject\n|-\n|Subject 1 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# English Core or English Elective\n# Hindi Core or Hindi Elective\n|-\n|Subject 2 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# Any 1 language from Group-L not opted as 'Subject 1'\n# Any 1 subject from Group-A\n|-\n|Subject 3, Subject 4, Subject 5 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# Any 3 subjects from Group-A\n# Any 3 subjects from Group-S\n# Any 3 subjects from combination of Group-A and Group-S\n|-\n|Subject 6 (optional)\n|Any 1 subject or language from any subject group not opted as subjects 1-5\n|-\n|Subject 7, Subject 8, Subject 9 (subjects of internal assessment; to be taken by regular candidates only)\n|\n# General Studies\n# Health and Physical Education\n# Work Experience\n|}\n\n==History==\n=== AISSCE 2014 ===\nAISSCE 2014 for Class 12 was conducted by the Central Board of Secondary Education between March 1, 2014 and April 25, 2014. The results were declared on May 26, 2014 (for Chennai and Thiruvananthapuram regions); May 28, 2014 (for Ajmer, Allahabad, Bhubaneshwar, Guwahati, Panchkula, and Patna regions); and May 29, 2014 (for Delhi and Dehradun regions).<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Post%20result%20Press%20Note%20Class%20XII-2014-Eng.pdf|title=Press Note: May 29, 2014|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2014|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\nIn 2014, the Board introduced the provision of 'revaluation' at the Senior Secondary Level, for those candidates who applied for verification of marks and for obtaining photocopy of the evaluated answer book. Revaluation could be applied online in maximum 10 questions each in the subjects of English Core, Functional English, English Elective, Hindi Core, Hindi Elective, Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, Biology, Business Studies, Economics and Accountancy.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2014<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%20for%20class%2012th%20-%20Stat.%202014(2).pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2014|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2014|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|8602\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3041\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1028928\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1007322\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|82.66%\n|}\n=== AISSCE 2015 ===\nThe duration of examination was from March 2, 2015 to April 20, 2015; and the results were declared on May 25, 2015 for all regions. The overall pass percentage in the Thiruvananthapuram region was 95.41%, making it the highest as compared to other regions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%202015%20(english).pdf|title=Press Note: May 25, 2015|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2015|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2015<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%20for%20class%2012th%20-%20Stat.%202015.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2015|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2015|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|9406\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3163\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1040515\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1016369\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|82%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2016 ===\nThe examination was conducted between March 1, 2016 and April 26, 2016; and the results were announced on May 21, 2016 for all regions. The top performing regions were Thiruvananthapuram and Chennai, with pass percentages 97.61% and 92.63% respectively.\n<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/PRESS%20NOTE%20(XII),%202016%20all%20regions_new_post_result.pdf|title=Press Note: May 21, 2016|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2016|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2016<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/PRESS%20NOTE%202016%20FOR%20CLASS%20XII%20(stat).pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2016|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2016|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|10093\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3757\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1065179\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1041482\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.05%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2017 ===\nThe examination commenced on March 9, 2017 and lasted upto April 29, 2017. The exams were postponed by one week in the states of Punjab, Goa, Manipur, Uttarakhand, and Uttar Pradesh due to state assembly elections. The results for all regions were, however, declared together on May 28, 2017. The CBSE organized post-result counselling sessions for students from May 28, 2017 to June 11, 2017.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/Press%20Note%20-%20Class%20XII%20Results%20(English).pdf|title=Press Note: May 28, 2017|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2017\n|Total number of schools\n|10673\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3504\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1096317\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1076760\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2018 ===\nThe Central Board of Secondary Education declared the results of the Senior School Certificate Examination for Class 12 on May 26, 2018.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/PRESS%20RELEASE-2018%20XII%20Declaration.pdf|title=Press Note: May 25, 2018|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2018|isbn=|location=New Delhi|pages=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2018<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/statistics-12-2018.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2018|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2018|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|11510\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|4145\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1119248\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1106772\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|918763\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.01%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2019 ===\nThe Senior School Certificate Examination for Class 12 commenced on February 15, 2019 and lasted upto April 4, 2019. The results for the same were declared on May 2, 2019. Hansika Shukla from Ghaziabad and Karishma Arora from Muzaffarnagar topped the exam, scoring 499 out of 500 marks. The top three performing regions were Thiruvananthapuram, Chennai, and New Delhi, with the pass percentages being 98.2%, 92.93%, and 91.87% respectively.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Varma|first=Shylaja|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/cbse-results-2019-cbse-class-12-results-declared-2-girls-hansika-shukla-karishma-arora-joint-toppers-2031825|title=CBSE Class 12 Results Declared, 2 Girls Are Joint Toppers|date=2019-05-03|work=NDTV|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2019<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/Press%20Note%20Class%20XII%20-%202019.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2019|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2019|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|12441\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|4627\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1218393\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1205484\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|1005427\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.4%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2020 ===\nThe Class 12 annual examinations commenced on February 15, 2020. \n\nDue to the [[2020 Delhi riots|riots in North East Delhi]], the Central Board of Secondary education cancelled all examinations that were scheduled from February 26, 2020 to February 29, 2020. <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/Press%20Note%2001.03.2020.pdf|title=Press Note: March 1, 2020|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2019|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> Amid the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus outbreak]], the CBSE also postponed all examinations that were to be held from March 19, 2020 to March 31, 2020. On April 1, 2020, it was announced that all remaining CBSE examinations in foreign countries would be cancelled, and an alternative system of marking and assessment would be given.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/PRESS RELEASE 01.04.20.pdf|title=Press Note: April 1, 2020|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2020<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/CBSE%20EXAM%202020%20DETAILS%20(2).pdf|title=CBSE Exam 2020 Details|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2019|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|13119; 143 foreign\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|4983; 72 foreign\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1206893; 15980 foreign\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|\n|}\n\n\n==Examination==\nEach subject in the examination is graded out of 100 marks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cbse.nic.in/curric~1/qpms2016/ms-2016.html|title=CBSE Marking scheme 2016 Class XII}}</ref> For subjects like physics, chemistry, mathematics, biology, etc. in which practical exams are also conducted, 30/20 marks are reserved for practicals and internals and 70/80 marks for the theory exams. From 2020,even in subjects like English, political science, regional languages, etc., CBSE issued guidelines to conduct internal assessment for 20 marks for which only the theory exam filled up the 100 marks limit up till 2019. Theory papers are conducted for a duration of 3 hours, while the duration for practical exams depends on the subject. \n\nCBSE issued guidelines for the addition of practical marks to mathematics in March 2019\n<ref>https://furiousboy.com/cbse-introduces-20-marks-practical-for-class-12-mathematics/</ref>\nFor practical exams, students have to perform practicals in other schools usually given by CBSE at random in the nearby state or area, maintain their records and attend a viva. The CBSE gives a list of practicals from which students are asked to perform practicals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/articles/key-guidelines-for-cbse-class-12-physics-practical-1392464571-1|title=CBSE Class 12 Physics Practical marking scheme}}</ref>\n\n==Result==\nThe result of the examinations is declared in the first week of May. In general, the passing percentage is around 80%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/education/cbse-results-cbse-class-12-results-declared-at-cbse-nic-in-2811689/|title=CBSE Class 12 Results}}</ref> The Delhi High Court has directed the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]] and [[Delhi University]] to discuss the ways by which the results of Main Exam, Revaluation, and Compartment Exam can be declared earlier than usual so that candidates do not miss the cut-off dates.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cbse.nic.in/ CBSE Website]\n\n[[Category: Central Board of Secondary Education]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox examination\n| name                = All India Senior School Certificate Examination\n| image_name          = [[File: CBSE_Logo.jpg]]\n| image_size          = 200px\n| image_alt           = Central Board of Secondary Education\n| caption             = Central Board of Secondary Education\n| acronym             = AISSCE\n| type                = Paper-based standardized test\n| test_admin          = [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]\n| skills_tested       = Languages, Humanities, Mathematics, Sciences, Skill Subjects, General Studies, Health and Physical Education, Work Experience\n| purpose             = Admission to undergraduate programs in universities or colleges\n| year_started        = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY}} -->\n| year_terminated     = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| duration            = 3 hours (per subject)\n| score_range         = 165-500\n| score_validity      = \n| offered             = Yearly\n| attempt_restriction =\n| regions             = '''India:'''<br>Delhi<br>Chennai<br>Guwahati<br>Ajmer<br>Panchkula<br>Allahabad<br>Patna<br>Bhubaneswar<br>Thiruvananthapuram<br>Dehradun<br><br>'''Middle East:'''<br>Bahrain<br>Iran<br>Oman<br>Qatar<br>Saudi Arabia<br>United Arab Emirates<br>Yemen<br><br>'''Foreign:'''<br>Afghanistan<br>Bangladesh<br>Burma<br>Ethiopia<br>Indonesia<br>Iran<br>Japan<br>Kuwait<br>Libya<br>Malaysia<br>Nepal<br>Nigeria<br>Republic of Benin<br>Russia<br>Singapore<br>Tanzania<br>Thailand<br>Uganda<br>West Africa\n| language            = English/Hindi\n| test_takers         = 1218393 (2019)\n| prerequisite        = Intended for Class 12 Students in CBSE-affiliated institutions\n| fee                 =  \n| score_users         = Colleges and universities; for undergraduate programs\n| qualification_rate  = 83.4% (2019)\n| free_label          = \n| free                = \n| website             = {{URL|cbse.nic.in}}\n| footnotes           =  \n}}\n\nThe '''All India Senior School Certificate Examination''' (AISSCE), colloquially known as the '''12<sup>th</sup> boards''', is a [[standardized test|standardized high-school completion examination]] conducted every year by the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]. The AISSCE assesses Class 12 students enrolled in CBSE-affiliated institutions. It is widely used for admissions to undergraduate programs in colleges and universities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://school.careers360.com/exams/cbse-class-12th?utm_source=google&utm_medium=kg|title=Central Board of Secondary Education Class 12th Examination|last=|first=|date=|website=Careers360|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nCBSE requires students to take five subjects which are externally assessed in Class 12, plus some internally assessed subjects (general studies, work experience and physical and health education). Students must pass each subject to gain their full qualification. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qips.ucas.com/qip/india-higher-secondary-school-certificate|title=India: Higher Secondary School Certificate|last=|first=|date=|website=UCAS Qualification Information Profiles|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n=== External Assessment ===\nThe Senior School Certificate Examination covers the entire syllabus of Class 12. Grades are awarded on the basis of a 9-point grading system in each scholastic subject as follows: <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=18-19}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\nGrading Scale for Scholastic Areas\n!Grade\n!Criteria\n|-\n|A1\n|Top {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|A2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|B1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|B2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|C1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|C2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|D1\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|D2\n|Next {{frac|1|8}}<sup>th</sup> of the passed candidates\n|-\n|E\n|(Unspecified)\n|}\n\n=== Internal Assessment ===\nInternal Assessment in different subjects will be as per details given in the syllabus for each subject:\n\n==== Assessment of Co-Scholastic Areas ====\nStudents are assessed on three areas, i.e. General Studies, Health and Physical Education, and Work Experience.\n\n== Subjects ==\nStudents can choose a minimum of five subjects in Class 11, for which they are required to write the AISSCE in Class 12. \n\nSubjects are offered as follows:<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=13-18}}</ref>\n\n==== Languages (Group-L)====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 001: English Elective\n* 301: English Core\n* 002: Hindi Elective\n* 302: Hindi Core\n* 003: Urdu Elective\n* 303: Urdu Core\n* 022: Sanskrit Elective\n* 322: Sanskrit Core\n* 104: Punjabi\n* 105: Bengali\n* 106: Tamil\n* 107: Telugu\n* 108: Sindhi\n* 109: Marathi\n* 110: Gujarati\n* 111: Manipuri\n* 112: Malayalam\n* 113: Odia\n* 114: Assamese\n* 115: Kannada\n* 116: Arabic\n* 117: Tibetan\n* 118: French\n* 120: German\n* 121: Russian\n* 123: Persian\n* 124: Nepali\n* 125: Limboo\n* 126: Lepcha\n* 189: Telugu Telangana\n* 192: Bodo\n* 193: Tangkhul\n* 194: Japanese\n* 195: Bhutia\n* 196: Spanish\n* 197: Kashmiri\n* 198: Mizo\n{{div col end}}\n\n==== Academic Subjects (Group-A) ====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 027: History\n* 028: Political Science\n* 029: Geography\n* 030: Economics\n* 031: Carnatic Music Vocal\n* 032: Carnatic Music Mel. Ins.\n* 033: Carnatic Per. Ins. Mridangam\n* 034: Hindustani Music Vocal\n* 035: Hindustani Music Mel. Ins.\n* 036: Hindustani Per. Ins.\n* 037: Psychology\n* 039: Sociology\n* 041: Mathematics\n* 241: Applied Mathematics\n* 042: Physics\n* 043: Chemistry\n* 044: Biology\n* 045: Biotechnology\n* 046: Engineering Graphics\n* 048: Physical Education\n* 049: Painting\n* 050: Graphics\n* 051: Sculpture\n* 052: Applied/Commercial Art\n* 054: Business Studies\n* 055: Accountancy\n* 056: Kathak (Dance)\n* 057: Bharatnatyam (Dance)\n* 058: Kuchipudi (Dance)\n* 059: Odissi (Dance)\n* 060: Manipuri (Dance)\n* 061: Kathakali (Dance)\n* 064: Home Science\n* 065: Informatics Practices\n* 083: Computer Science\n* 066: Entrepreneurship\n* 073: Knowledge Tradition and Practices of India\n* 074: Legal Studies\n* 076: National Cadet Corps (NCC)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==== Skill Subjects (Group-S) ====\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n* 802: Information Technology\n* 803: Web Application\n* 804: Automotive\n* 805: Financial Markets Management\n* 806: Tourism\n* 807: Beauty and Wellness\n* 808: Agriculture\n* 809: Food Production\n* 810: Front Office Operations\n* 811: Banking\n* 812: Marketing\n* 813: Health Care\n* 814: Insurance\n* 816: Horticulture\n* 817: Typography and Computer Application\n* 818: Geospatial Technology\n* 819: Electrical Technology\n* 820: Electronic Technology\n* 821: Media\n* 822: Taxation\n* 823: Cost Accounting\n* 824: Office Procedures and Practices\n* 825: Shorthand (English)\n* 826: Shorthand (Hindi)\n* 827: Air-conditioning and Refrigeration\n* 828: Medical Diagnostics\n* 829: Textile Design\n* 830: Design\n* 831: Salesmanship\n* 833: Business Administration\n* 834: Food Nutrition and Dietetics\n* 835: Mass Media Studies\n* 836: Library and Information Science\n* 837: Fashion Studies\n* 841: Yoga\n* 842: Early Childhood Education\n* 843: Artificial Intelligence\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Combination of Subjects===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Combination of Subjects <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbseacademic.nic.in/web_material/CurriculumMain21/SrSecondary/Intitial_pages_srsec_2020-21.pdf|title=Senior School Curriculum - Class XI-XII (2020-21)|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2020|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=11-12}}</ref>\n!Serial No.\n!Name of Subject\n|-\n|Subject 1 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# English Core or English Elective\n# Hindi Core or Hindi Elective\n|-\n|Subject 2 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# Any 1 language from Group-L not opted as 'Subject 1'\n# Any 1 subject from Group-A\n|-\n|Subject 3, Subject 4, Subject 5 (compulsory)\n|Any 1 from the following:\n\n# Any 3 subjects from Group-A\n# Any 3 subjects from Group-S\n# Any 3 subjects from combination of Group-A and Group-S\n|-\n|Subject 6 (optional)\n|Any 1 subject or language from any subject group not opted as subjects 1-5\n|-\n|Subject 7, Subject 8, Subject 9 (subjects of internal assessment; to be taken by regular candidates only)\n|\n# General Studies\n# Health and Physical Education\n# Work Experience\n|}\n\n==History==\n=== AISSCE 2014 ===\nAISSCE 2014 for Class 12 was conducted by the Central Board of Secondary Education between March 1, 2014 and April 25, 2014. The results were declared on May 26, 2014 (for Chennai and Thiruvananthapuram regions); May 28, 2014 (for Ajmer, Allahabad, Bhubaneshwar, Guwahati, Panchkula, and Patna regions); and May 29, 2014 (for Delhi and Dehradun regions).<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Post%20result%20Press%20Note%20Class%20XII-2014-Eng.pdf|title=Press Note: May 29, 2014|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2014|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\nIn 2014, the Board introduced the provision of 'revaluation' at the Senior Secondary Level, for those candidates who applied for verification of marks and for obtaining photocopy of the evaluated answer book. Revaluation could be applied online in maximum 10 questions each in the subjects of English Core, Functional English, English Elective, Hindi Core, Hindi Elective, Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, Biology, Business Studies, Economics and Accountancy.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2014<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%20for%20class%2012th%20-%20Stat.%202014(2).pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2014|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2014|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|8602\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3041\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1028928\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1007322\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|82.66%\n|}\n=== AISSCE 2015 ===\nThe duration of examination was from March 2, 2015 to April 20, 2015; and the results were declared on May 25, 2015 for all regions. The overall pass percentage in the Thiruvananthapuram region was 95.41%, making it the highest as compared to other regions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%202015%20(english).pdf|title=Press Note: May 25, 2015|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2015|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2015<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/Press%20Note%20for%20class%2012th%20-%20Stat.%202015.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2015|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2015|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|9406\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3163\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1040515\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1016369\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|82%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2016 ===\nThe examination was conducted between March 1, 2016 and April 26, 2016; and the results were announced on May 21, 2016 for all regions. The top performing regions were Thiruvananthapuram and Chennai, with pass percentages 97.61% and 92.63% respectively.\n<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/attach/PRESS%20NOTE%20(XII),%202016%20all%20regions_new_post_result.pdf|title=Press Note: May 21, 2016|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2016|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2016<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/PRESS%20NOTE%202016%20FOR%20CLASS%20XII%20(stat).pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2016|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2016|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|10093\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3757\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1065179\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1041482\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.05%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2017 ===\nThe examination commenced on March 9, 2017 and lasted upto April 29, 2017. The exams were postponed by one week in the states of Punjab, Goa, Manipur, Uttarakhand, and Uttar Pradesh due to state assembly elections. The results for all regions were, however, declared together on May 28, 2017. The CBSE organized post-result counselling sessions for students from May 28, 2017 to June 11, 2017.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/Press%20Note%20-%20Class%20XII%20Results%20(English).pdf|title=Press Note: May 28, 2017|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2017\n|Total number of schools\n|10673\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|3504\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1096317\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1076760\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2018 ===\nThe Central Board of Secondary Education declared the results of the Senior School Certificate Examination for Class 12 on May 26, 2018.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/PRESS%20RELEASE-2018%20XII%20Declaration.pdf|title=Press Note: May 25, 2018|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2018|isbn=|location=New Delhi|pages=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for AISSCE 2018<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/statistics-12-2018.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2018|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2018|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|11510\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|4145\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1119248\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1106772\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|918763\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.01%\n|}\n\n=== AISSCE 2019 ===\nThe Senior School Certificate Examination for Class 12 commenced on February 15, 2019 and lasted upto April 4, 2019. The results for the same were declared on May 2, 2019. Hansika Shukla from Ghaziabad and Karishma Arora from Muzaffarnagar topped the exam, scoring 499 out of 500 marks. The top three performing regions were Thiruvananthapuram, Chennai, and New Delhi, with the pass percentages being 98.2%, 92.93%, and 91.87% respectively.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Varma|first=Shylaja|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/cbse-results-2019-cbse-class-12-results-declared-2-girls-hansika-shukla-karishma-arora-joint-toppers-2031825|title=CBSE Class 12 Results Declared, 2 Girls Are Joint Toppers|date=2019-05-03|work=NDTV|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Statistics for SSCE 2019<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/attach/Press%20Note%20Class%20XII%20-%202019.pdf|title=Senior School Certificate Examination (Class XII) Result 2019|publisher=Central Board of Secondary Education|year=2019|isbn=|location=New Delhi, India|pages=}}</ref>\n|Total number of schools\n|12441\n|-\n|Total number of exam centers\n|4627\n|-\n|Total number of registered candidates\n|1218393\n|-\n|Total number of candidates appeared\n|1205484\n|-\n|Total number of candidates passed\n|1005427\n|-\n|Pass percentage\n|83.4%\n|}\n\n== AISSCE 2020 ==\n\n\n==Examination==\nEach subject in the examination is graded out of 100 marks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cbse.nic.in/curric~1/qpms2016/ms-2016.html|title=CBSE Marking scheme 2016 Class XII}}</ref> For subjects like physics, chemistry, mathematics, biology, etc. in which practical exams are also conducted, 30/20 marks are reserved for practicals and internals and 70/80 marks for the theory exams. From 2020,even in subjects like English, political science, regional languages, etc., CBSE issued guidelines to conduct internal assessment for 20 marks for which only the theory exam filled up the 100 marks limit up till 2019. Theory papers are conducted for a duration of 3 hours, while the duration for practical exams depends on the subject. \n\nCBSE issued guidelines for the addition of practical marks to mathematics in March 2019\n<ref>https://furiousboy.com/cbse-introduces-20-marks-practical-for-class-12-mathematics/</ref>\nFor practical exams, students have to perform practicals in other schools usually given by CBSE at random in the nearby state or area, maintain their records and attend a viva. The CBSE gives a list of practicals from which students are asked to perform practicals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/articles/key-guidelines-for-cbse-class-12-physics-practical-1392464571-1|title=CBSE Class 12 Physics Practical marking scheme}}</ref>\n\n==Result==\nThe result of the examinations is declared in the first week of May. In general, the passing percentage is around 80%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/education/cbse-results-cbse-class-12-results-declared-at-cbse-nic-in-2811689/|title=CBSE Class 12 Results}}</ref> The Delhi High Court has directed the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]] and [[Delhi University]] to discuss the ways by which the results of Main Exam, Revaluation, and Compartment Exam can be declared earlier than usual so that candidates do not miss the cut-off dates.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cbse.nic.in/ CBSE Website]\n\n[[Category: Central Board of Secondary Education]]\n", "name_user": "ZennieG", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added information on AISSCE 2020", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_India_Senior_School_Certificate_Examination"}
